	<div class="mw-indicators">
	</div>
	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" >LightDM</h1>


	<div id="bodyContent" class="vector-body">
			<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From ArchWiki</div>
		<div id="contentSub"></div>
		<div id="contentSub2"></div>
		
		<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content mw-content-ltr" lang="en" dir="ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><div class="archwiki-template-meta-related-articles-start"><p>Related articles</p><ul>
<li><a href="/title/Display_manager" title="Display manager">Display manager</a></li>
<li><a href="/title/GDM" title="GDM">GDM</a></li>
<li><a href="/title/LXDM" title="LXDM">LXDM</a></li>
</ul></div>
<p><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://github.com/canonical/lightdm">LightDM</a> is a cross-desktop <a href="/title/Display_manager" title="Display manager">display manager</a>. Its key features are:
</p>
<ul><li>Cross-desktop - supports different desktop technologies.</li>
<li>Supports different display technologies (X, Mir, Wayland ...).</li>
<li>Lightweight - low memory usage and high performance.</li>
<li>Supports guest sessions.</li>
<li>Supports remote login (incoming - <a href="/title/XDMCP" title="XDMCP">XDMCP</a>, <a href="/title/VNC" class="mw-redirect" title="VNC">VNC</a>, outgoing - XDMCP, <a href="/title/PAM" title="PAM">PAM</a>).</li>
<li>Comprehensive test suite.</li>
<li>Low code complexity.</li></ul>
<p>More details about LightDM's design can be found <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.freedesktop.org/wiki/Software/LightDM/Design">here</a>.
</p>
